{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb200 
On February 14, 2019, Plaintiff Debra Turner filed her First Amended Civil Complaint re Severed and Transferred Claims, etc. (ROA#123, hereafter, \u8220\'3fFAC\u8221\'3f). Nominal Defendant the Conrad Prebys Foundation (the \u8220\'3fFoundation\u8221\'3f) filed a Demurrer to the FAC (ROA#145). Defendant Laurie Anne Victoria (\u8220\'3fVictoria\u8221\'3f) filed a Demurrer to the FAC (ROA#151) and a Motion to Strike certain portions of the FAC (ROA#150). Defendants Joseph Gronotte (\u8220\'3fGronotte\u8221\'3f), Anthony Cortes (\u8220\'3fCortes\u8221\'3f), and Gregory Rogers (\u8220\'3fRogers\u8221\'3f) each filed Joinders in the Demurrers of the Foundation and/or Victoria (ROA#138, 141, 160, respectively). The demurrers and motion to strike were fully briefed and the Court heard oral argument on these matters on May 17, 2019. After the hearing, the Court took the matters under submission.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
