{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Conrad Prebys (Prebys) was a wealthy philanthropist. In addition to the Foundation, Prebys created an inter vivos trust, the Conrad Prebys Trust (the Trust). Prebys funded the Trust and directed it to make distributions to specific beneficiaries after his death. The assets remaining after the gift distributions were to \u8220\'3fgo to the Foundation to be used for charitable purposes.\u8221\'3f
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Under the Foundation\rquote s bylaws, all its directors were also members of the Foundation, and the Foundation had no other members. 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
Most of the directors 
}
{\b1 \cf1 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
