{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 had a personal relationship with Prebys. For instance, Victoria was the chief executive officer of a company Prebys owned, and plaintiff was Prebys\rquote s \u8220\'3flife partner, living [with Prebys] as a couple for over 16 years until his death\u8221\'3f in 2016.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In addition to her role at the Foundation, Victoria was the trustee of the Trust. At the initial meeting of the board of directors (Board) after Prebys\rquote s death, Victoria and an attorney informed the directors that Prebys\rquote s son, Eric Prebys, might contest the Trust.
}
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs20 
{\b1 \cf19 \f2 \i0 \fs16 
