{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
 Although Eric was originally a beneficiary under the Trust, Prebys eliminated the gift to Eric two years before he died. The Board was informed that Eric had hired counsel with the intention of challenging his disinheritance on the grounds that his father lacked mental competence and was unduly influenced by plaintiff.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ri0 \i0 \qj \fs20 \li0 
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
In her role as trustee, Victoria wanted to settle Eric\rquote s claims, and she discussed with the Board an appropriate settlement amount. Plaintiff was the only director who opposed such a settlement. The Board eventually voted to authorize a maximum settlement of $12 million plus the payment of estate taxes. In early 2017, Victoria, on behalf of the Trust, settled with Eric for a total sum of $15 million, paying $9 million to Eric directly and the remainder in taxes.
\par 
}
}
}
{\b0 \cf19 \f2 \ul0 \strike0 \i0 \fs20 \sa0 \sb0 
\u160\'3f
\par 
}
